{{Day}}

==Events==
*[[1284]] &amp;ndash; The Republic of [[Republic of Pisa|Pisa]] is defeated in the [[Battle of Meloria]] by the [[Republic of Genoa]], thus losing its naval dominance in the [[Mediterranean Sea|Mediterranean]].
*[[1506]] &amp;ndash; The [[Grand Duchy of Lithuania]] defeated the [[Crimean Khanate]] in the [[Battle of Kletsk]]
*[[1538]] &amp;ndash; [[Bogotá]], [[Colombia]], is founded by [[Gonzalo Jiménez de Quesada]].
*[[1661]] &amp;ndash; The [[Treaty of The Hague (1661)|Treaty of The Hague]] is signed by [[Portugal]] and the [[Dutch Republic]].
*[[1787]] &amp;ndash; Sixty proof sheets of the [[United States Constitution|Constitution of the United States]] are delivered to the [[Philadelphia Convention|Constitutional Convention]] in [[Philadelphia]].
*[[1806]] &amp;ndash; [[Francis II, Holy Roman Emperor|Francis II]], the last [[Holy Roman Emperor]], abdicates ending the [[Holy Roman Empire]].
*[[1819]] &amp;ndash; [[Norwich University]] is founded in [[Vermont]] as the first private military school in the [[United States]].
*[[1825]] &amp;ndash; [[Bolivia]] gains independence from [[Spain]].
*[[1845]] &amp;ndash; The [[Russian Geographical Society]] is founded in [[Saint Petersburg]].
*[[1861]] &amp;ndash; The [[United Kingdom]] annexes [[Lagos]], [[Nigeria]].
*[[1862]] &amp;ndash; [[American Civil War]]: the [[Confederate States of America|Confederate]] [[ironclad]] {{Ship|CSS|Arkansas}} is scuttled on the [[Mississippi River]] after suffering damage in a battle with {{USS|Essex|1856|6}} near [[Baton Rouge, Louisiana]].
*[[1870]] &amp;ndash; [[Franco-Prussian War]]: the [[Battle of Wörth (1870)|Battle of Wörth]] results in a decisive [[Kingdom of Prussia|Prussian]] victory.
*[[1890]] &amp;ndash; At [[Auburn Prison]] in [[New York State|New York]], murderer [[William Kemmler]] becomes the first person to be [[Capital punishment|executed]] by [[electric chair]].
*[[1901]] &amp;ndash; [[Kiowa]] land in [[Oklahoma]] is opened for white settlement, effectively dissolving the contiguous [[Indian reservation|reservation]].
*[[1909]] &amp;ndash; [[Alice Huyler Ramsey]] and three friends become the first women to complete a transcontinental auto trip.
*[[1912]] &amp;ndash; The [[Bull Moose Party]] meets at the [[Chicago Coliseum]].
*[[1914]] &amp;ndash; [[World War I]]: [[First Battle of the Atlantic]] &amp;ndash; two days after the [[United Kingdom]] had declared war on [[Germany]] over the German invasion of [[Belgium]], ten German [[U-boats]] leave their base in [[Helgoland]] to attack [[Royal Navy]] warships in the [[North Sea]].
*  1914   &amp;ndash; World War I: [[Serbia]] declares war on [[Germany]]; [[Austria]] declares war on [[Russia]].
*[[1915]] &amp;ndash; World War I: [[Battle of Sari Bair]] &amp;ndash; the [[Allies of World War I|Allies]] mount a diversionary attack timed to coincide with a major Allied landing of reinforcements at [[Suvla Bay]].
*[[1917]] &amp;ndash; World War I: [[Battle of Mărăşeşti]] between the [[Romania]]n and German armies begins.
*[[1926]] &amp;ndash; [[Gertrude Ederle]] becomes the first woman to swim across the [[English Channel]].
*  1926   &amp;ndash; In [[New York City]], the [[Warner Brothers]]' [[Vitaphone]] system premieres with the movie ''[[Don Juan (1926 film)|Don Juan]]'' starring [[John Barrymore]].
*  1926   &amp;ndash; [[Harry Houdini]] performs his greatest feat, spending 91 minutes underwater in a sealed tank before escaping.
*[[1930]] &amp;ndash; Judge [[Joseph Force Crater]] steps into a [[Taxicab|taxi]] in New York and disappears to be never seen again.
*[[1942]] &amp;ndash; Queen [[Wilhelmina of the Netherlands]] becomes the first reigning queen to address a joint session of the [[United States Congress]].
*[[1945]] &amp;ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Hiroshima]] is [[Atomic bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki|devastated]] when the [[nuclear weapon|atomic bomb]] &quot;[[Little Boy]]&quot; is dropped by the [[United States]] [[Boeing B-29|B-29]] ''[[Enola Gay]]''. Around 70,000 people are killed instantly, and some tens of thousands die in subsequent years from burns and [[radiation poisoning]].
*[[1956]] &amp;ndash; After going bankrupt in [[1955]], the [[United States|American]] broadcaster [[DuMont Television Network]] makes its final broadcast, a boxing match from [[St. Nicholas Rink|St. Nicholas Arena]] in New York in the ''[[Boxing from St. Nicholas Arena]]'' series.
*[[1960]] &amp;ndash; [[Cuban Revolution]]: in response to a [[United States embargo against Cuba|United States embargo]], [[Cuba]] nationalizes [[United States|American]] and foreign-owned property in the nation.
*[[1962]] &amp;ndash; [[Jamaica]] becomes independent.
*[[1964]] &amp;ndash; [[Prometheus (tree)|Prometheus]], a [[bristlecone pine]] and the world's oldest [[tree]], is cut down.
*[[1965]] &amp;ndash; [[President of the United States|US President]] [[Lyndon B. Johnson]] signs the [[Voting Rights Act of 1965]] into [[Law of the United States|law]].
*[[1966]] &amp;ndash; [[Braniff Airlines Flight 250]] crashes in [[Falls City, NE]] killing all 42 on board.
*[[1976]] &amp;ndash; [[Zulfikar Ali Bhutto]] lays the foundation stone of [[Port Qasim]], [[Karachi]].
*[[1986]] &amp;ndash; A low-pressure system that redeveloped off the [[New South Wales]] coast dumps a record 328 millimeters (13&amp;nbsp;inches) of rain in a day on [[Sydney]].
*[[1988]] &amp;ndash; The [[Tompkins Square Park Police Riot (1988)|Tompkins Square Park Police Riot]] in New York City spurs a reform of the [[NYPD]], held responsible for the event.
*[[1990]] &amp;ndash; [[Gulf War]]: the [[United Nations Security Council]] orders a global [[trade embargo]] against [[Iraq]] in response to Iraq's invasion of [[Kuwait]].
*[[1991]] &amp;ndash; [[Tim Berners-Lee]] releases files describing his idea for the [[World Wide Web]]. WWW debuts as a publicly available service on the [[Internet]].
*  1991   &amp;ndash; [[Doi Takako]], chair of the [[Social Democratic Party (Japan)|Social Democratic Party]], becomes [[Japan]]'s first female speaker of the [[House of Representatives of Japan|House of Representatives]].
*[[1993]] &amp;ndash; Heavy rains and debris kill 72 in the [[Kagoshima]] and [[Aira]] areas of [[Kyūshū]], [[Japan]].
*[[1996]] &amp;ndash; [[NASA]] announces that the [[ALH 84001]] meteorite, thought to originate from [[Mars]], contains evidence of primitive life-forms.
*[[1997]] &amp;ndash; [[Korean Air Flight 801]], a [[Boeing 747]]-300, crashes into the jungle on [[Guam]] on approach to airport, killing 228.
*[[2008]] &amp;ndash;  A military junta led by [[Mohamed Ould Abdel Aziz]] stages a [[2008 Mauritanian coup d'état|coup d'état]] in [[Mauritania]], overthrowing president [[Sidi Ould Cheikh Abdallahi]].
*[[2010]] &amp;ndash; The [[Conservative – Liberal Democrat coalition agreement|incoming coalition government]] of the [[United Kingdom]] discontinues the use of the controversial [[ContactPoint]] database of children.

