{{ThisDateInRecentYears}} 
{{Day}}

==Events==
*[[480 BC]] &amp;ndash; [[Greco-Persian Wars]]: [[Battle of Artemisium]] &amp;ndash; the [[Persian Empire|Persians]] win a naval victory over the [[Greeks]] in an engagement fought near [[Artemisium]], a promontory on the north coast of [[Euboea]].
*[[48 BC]] &amp;ndash; [[Caesar's civil war]]: [[Battle of Pharsalus]] &amp;ndash; [[Julius Caesar]] decisively defeats [[Pompey]] at [[Pharsalus]] and Pompey flees to [[Ancient Egypt|Egypt]].
* [[378]] &amp;ndash; [[Gothic War (376-382)|Gothic War]]: [[Battle of Adrianople]] &amp;ndash; A large [[Roman Empire|Roman]] army led by Emperor [[Valens]] is defeated by the [[Visigoths]] in present-day [[Turkey]]. Valens is killed along with over half of his army.
* [[681]] &amp;ndash; [[Bulgaria]] is founded as a [[Khanate]] on the south bank of the [[Danube]] after defeating the [[Byzantine Empire|Byzantine]] armies of Emperor [[Constantine IV]] south of the [[Danube]] delta.
*[[1173]] &amp;ndash; Construction of the [[campanile]] of the [[cathedral]] of [[Pisa]] (now known as the [[Leaning Tower of Pisa]]) begins; it will take two centuries to complete.
*[[1329]] &amp;ndash; [[Kollam|Quilon]], the first [[Christianity in India|Indian Christian Diocese]], is erected by [[Pope John XXII]]; the French-born [[Jordanus]] is appointed the first Bishop.
*[[1483]] &amp;ndash; Opening of the [[Sistine Chapel]] in [[Rome]] with the celebration of a [[Mass (liturgy)|Mass]].
*[[1810]] &amp;ndash; [[Napoleon I of France|Napoleon]] annexes [[Westphalia]] as part of the [[First French Empire]].
*[[1814]] &amp;ndash; [[Indian Wars]]: the [[Muscogee (Creek)|Creek]] sign the [[Treaty of Fort Jackson]], giving up huge parts of [[Alabama]] and [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]].
*[[1842]] &amp;ndash; The [[Webster-Ashburton Treaty]] is signed, establishing the [[United States]]-[[Canada]] border east of the [[Rocky Mountains]].
*[[1854]] &amp;ndash; [[Henry David Thoreau]] published ''[[Walden]]''.
*[[1862]] &amp;ndash; [[American Civil War]]: [[Battle of Cedar Mountain]] &amp;ndash; At [[Culpeper County, Virginia|Cedar Mountain, Virginia]], [[Confederate States of America|Confederate]] General [[Thomas J. Jackson|Stonewall Jackson]] narrowly defeats [[United States|Union]] forces under General [[John Pope (military officer)|John Pope]].
*[[1877]] &amp;ndash; [[Indian Wars]]: [[Battle of Big Hole]] &amp;ndash; A small band of [[Nez Percé]] Indians clash with the [[United States Army]].
*[[1892]] &amp;ndash; [[Thomas Edison]] receives a [[patent]] for a two-way [[Telegraphy|telegraph]].
*[[1902]] &amp;ndash; [[Edward VII of the United Kingdom|Edward VII]] and [[Alexandra of Denmark]] are crowned [[List of British monarchs|King]] and [[List of British consorts|Queen]] of the [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland]].
*[[1907]] &amp;ndash; The first [[Boy Scout]] [[Brownsea Island Scout camp|encampment]] concludes at [[Brownsea Island]] in southern England.
*[[1925]] &amp;ndash; A [[Kakori train robbery|train robbery]] takes place in [[Kakori]], near [[Lucknow]], [[India]]
*[[1930]] &amp;ndash; [[Betty Boop]] made her cartoon debut in ''[[Dizzy Dishes]]''.
*[[1936]] &amp;ndash; [[Summer Olympic Games]]: [[1936 Summer Olympics|Games of the XI Olympiad]] &amp;ndash; [[Jesse Owens]] wins his fourth [[gold medal]] at the games becoming the first American to win four medals in one [[Olympiad]].
*[[1942]] &amp;ndash; [[India]]n leader [[Mahatma Gandhi]] is arrested in [[Bombay]] by [[United Kingdom|British]] forces, launching the [[Quit India Movement]].
*  1942   &amp;ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Battle of Savo Island]] &amp;ndash; [[Allies of World War II|Allied]] naval forces protecting their amphibious forces during the initial stages of the [[Battle of Guadalcanal]] are surprised and defeated by an [[Imperial Japanese Navy]] cruiser force.
*[[1944]] &amp;ndash; The [[United States Forest Service]] and the Wartime Advertising Council release posters featuring [[Smokey Bear]] for the first time.
*  1944   &amp;ndash; [[Continuation war]]: The [[Vyborg–Petrozavodsk Offensive]], the largest offensive launched by Soviet Union against Finland during the Second World War, ends to a strategic stalemate. Both Finnish and Soviet troops at the Finnish front dug to defensive positions, and the front remains stable until the end of the war.
*[[1945]] &amp;ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Nagasaki, Nagasaki|Nagasaki]] is [[Atomic bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki|devastated]] when an [[nuclear weapon|atomic bomb]], ''[[Fat Man]]'', is dropped by the [[United States]] [[B-29 Superfortress|B-29]] ''[[Bockscar]]''. 39,000 people are killed outright.
*[[1965]] &amp;ndash; [[Singapore]] is [[History of the Republic of Singapore#Independence of Singapore|expelled]] from [[Malaysia]] and becomes the first and only country to date to gain independence unwillingly.
*  1965   &amp;ndash; A fire at a [[LGM-25C Titan II|Titan]] missile base near [[Searcy, Arkansas]] kills 53 construction workers.
*[[1969]] &amp;ndash; Members of a [[cult]] led by [[Charles Manson]] brutally murder pregnant actress [[Sharon Tate]] (wife of [[Roman Polanski]]), [[coffee]] heiress [[Abigail Folger]], Polish actor [[Wojciech Frykowski]], men's hairstylist [[Jay Sebring]] and recent high-school graduate [[Steven Parent]].
*[[1971]] &amp;ndash; [[The Troubles]]: The [[British security forces]] in [[Northern Ireland]] launch [[Operation Demetrius]]. Hundreds of people are arrested and [[Internment|interned]], thousands are displaced, and twenty are killed in the violence that follows.
*[[1974]] &amp;ndash; As a direct result of the [[Watergate scandal]], [[Richard Nixon]] becomes the first [[President of the United States]] to resign from office. His [[Vice President of the United States of America|Vice President]], [[Gerald Ford]], becomes president.
*[[1977]] &amp;ndash; The military-controlled Government of [[Uruguay]] announces that it will return the nation to civilian rule through general elections in [[1981]] for a President and [[General Assembly of Uruguay|Congress]].
*[[1988]] &amp;ndash; [[Wayne Gretzky]] is traded from the [[Edmonton Oilers]] to the [[Los Angeles Kings]] in one of the most controversial player transactions in [[ice hockey]] history, upsetting many Canadians so much that some considered him a &quot;traitor&quot; to his home country.
*[[1993]] &amp;ndash; The [[Liberal Democratic Party (Japan)|Liberal Democratic Party of Japan]] loses a 38-year hold on national leadership.
*[[1999]] &amp;ndash; [[Russia]]n President [[Boris Yeltsin]] fires his Prime Minister, [[Sergei Stepashin]], and for the fourth time fires his entire cabinet.
*  1999   &amp;ndash; The [[Diet of Japan]] enacts a law establishing the [[Flag of Japan|Hinomaru]] and [[Kimi Ga Yo]] as the official [[national flag]] and [[national anthem]].
*[[2001]] &amp;ndash; US President [[George W. Bush]] announces his support for federal funding of limited research on embryonic [[stem cell]]s.

